8. Bridge Action Interface

The Director Agent interacts with the bridge through structured commands.

Instantiate

Create object.

instantiate(object_class="tower", location="district_west")

Modify

Change attributes.

modify(uuid="obj_147", material="blue_glass")

Relocate

Change location.

relocate(uuid="obj_147", anchor="hill_top")

Restyle

Apply perceptual changes.

restyle(uuid="obj_147", style="gothic")

Reconcile

Resolve semantic conflicts.

reconcile(parameter="sky_state", policy="branch_timeline")


⸻

9. Conflict Resolution

Conflicts arise when commands contradict.

Examples:
	•	day vs night
	•	duplicate object identities
	•	impossible physics requests

Resolution strategies:
	•	last command wins
	•	invariant priority
	•	timeline branching
	•	layered coexistence

Mirror typically arbitrates.

⸻

10. Performance Strategy

To manage compute cost, IWDS uses fidelity tiers.

Tier	Scope	Representation
Tier 1	distant world	symbolic geometry
Tier 2	interactive region	spatial runtime objects
Tier 3	focal region	neural high-detail rendering

Compute follows attention.

