12. Key Technical Challenges

World Consistency

Maintaining identity across generative updates.

Latency

Target <500ms for command response.

Scene Memory

Large worlds require summarized state representation.

Compute Cost

Dynamic world generation is expensive.

Semantic Conflict Resolution

Commands may contradict world invariants.

⸻

13. Long-Term Vision

IWDS transforms generative AI from a content generator into a world engine.

Users will not generate artifacts.

They will enter simulations and direct them conversationally.

Film, game engines, and AI generation converge into a single creative medium.

